   "id": "0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    "  \"cells\": [\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Crystallographic Phase Retrieval\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"This notebook demonstrates **phase retrieval for X-ray crystallography** using the same\\n\",\n",
    "        \"iterative projection algorithms used for astronomical wavefront sensing.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"## The Crystallographic Phase Problem\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"When X-rays scatter off a crystal lattice, the detector records **diffraction intensities**\\n\",\n",
    "        \"$|F(\\\\mathbf{h})|^2$ but loses the **phase** $\\\\varphi(\\\\mathbf{h})$. Recovering these phases\\n\",\n",
    "        \"from measured intensities alone is the *crystallographic phase problem* — one of the\\n\",\n",
    "        \"foundational challenges in structural biology and materials science.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"We demonstrate the complete pipeline:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"1. **Download** a real crystal structure from the Crystallography Open Database (COD)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"2. **Parse** the CIF file and extract unit-cell parameters + atom sites\\n\",\n",
    "        \"3. **Simulate** a 2-D diffraction pattern from the structure factors\\n\",\n",
    "        \"4. **Run** iterative phase retrieval algorithms (ER, HIO, RAAR, WF)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"5. **Visualise** recovered phases, electron density, and convergence\\n\",\n",
    "        \"6. **Compare** algorithm performance using the crystallographic R-factor\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"import matplotlib\\n\",\n",
    "        \"matplotlib.use('Agg')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "        \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "        \"from pathlib import Path\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Phase retrieval modules\\n\",\n",
    "        \"from src.data.crystallography import (\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    available_cod_presets,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    parse_cif,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    simulate_diffraction,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    run_crystallography_retrieval,\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"from src.models.crystallography import AtomSite, CrystalStructure\\n\",\n",
    "        \"from src.visualization.crystallography_plots import (\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_diffraction_pattern,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_crystallography_result,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_crystal_summary,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_electron_density,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_r_factor_comparison,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    plot_crystallography_comparison,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    save_figure,\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"OUTPUT_DIR = Path('notebooks/outputs')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"OUTPUT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"GRID_SIZE = 128\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('Available COD presets:')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"for key, desc in available_cod_presets().items():\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    print(f'  {key:15s} — {desc}')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 1. Crystal Structure: NaCl (Rock Salt)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"We start with Sodium Chloride — one of the most studied crystal structures.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"The face-centred cubic (FCC) lattice with space group **Fm-3m** has Na at the\\n\",\n",
    "        \"origin and Cl at (½, ½, ½).\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Define NaCl structure directly (no network needed)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"nacl = CrystalStructure(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    cod_id='1000041',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    formula='NaCl',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    space_group='F m -3 m',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    a=5.6400, b=5.6400, c=5.6400,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    alpha=90.0, beta=90.0, gamma=90.0,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    atoms=[\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='Na1', symbol='Na', x=0.0, y=0.0, z=0.0),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='Cl1', symbol='Cl', x=0.5, y=0.5, z=0.5),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    ],\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Crystal: {nacl.formula}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Space group: {nacl.space_group}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Unit cell: a={nacl.a:.4f} Å, b={nacl.b:.4f} Å, c={nacl.c:.4f} Å')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Angles: α={nacl.alpha}°, β={nacl.beta}°, γ={nacl.gamma}°')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Atoms: {len(nacl.atoms)}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"for atom in nacl.atoms:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    print(f'  {atom.label}: {atom.symbol} at ({atom.x:.4f}, {atom.y:.4f}, {atom.z:.4f})')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 2. Simulate Diffraction Pattern\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"We compute the 2-D structure factors $F(h,k)$ for the $l=0$ reciprocal-space\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plane, then plot the diffraction intensities $|F(h,k)|^2$ with a thermal\\n\",\n",
    "        \"(Debye-Waller) damping factor.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Simulate diffraction\\n\",\n",
    "        \"pattern = simulate_diffraction(nacl, grid_size=GRID_SIZE)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Diffraction pattern shape: {pattern.image.shape}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Total intensity: {pattern.image.sum():.6f}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Max intensity: {pattern.image.max():.6e}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Space group: {pattern.space_group}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Plot\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_diffraction_pattern(pattern)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_diffraction_nacl.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('Saved: cryst_diffraction_nacl.png')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 3. Phase Retrieval with HIO\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"We run the **Hybrid Input-Output (HIO)** algorithm on the simulated diffraction\\n\",\n",
    "        \"pattern to recover the lost phases. The algorithm iterates between the\\n\",\n",
    "        \"reciprocal-space constraint (measured amplitudes) and a real-space support\\n\",\n",
    "        \"constraint.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Run HIO phase retrieval\\n\",\n",
    "        \"result_hio = run_crystallography_retrieval(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    pattern,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    algorithm_name='hio',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    max_iterations=200,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    beta=0.9,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    random_seed=42,\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Algorithm: {result_hio.algorithm.value.upper()}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Iterations: {result_hio.n_iterations}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Converged: {result_hio.converged}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'R-factor: {result_hio.r_factor:.4f}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Time: {result_hio.elapsed_seconds:.2f}s')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Full result plot\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_crystallography_result(pattern, result_hio)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_result_hio.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Summary\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_crystal_summary(pattern, result_hio)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_summary_hio.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('Saved: cryst_result_hio.png, cryst_summary_hio.png')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 4. Algorithm Comparison\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"We compare four phase-retrieval algorithms on the same NaCl diffraction data:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- **ER** (Error Reduction) — monotone convergence, slow\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- **HIO** (Hybrid Input-Output) — fast escape from local minima\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- **RAAR** (Relaxed Averaged Alternating Reflections) — robust convergence\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- **WF** (Wirtinger Flow) — gradient-based, provably optimal\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"algorithms = ['er', 'hio', 'raar', 'wf']\\n\",\n",
    "        \"results = {}\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"for alg in algorithms:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    res = run_crystallography_retrieval(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        pattern,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        algorithm_name=alg,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        max_iterations=200,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        random_seed=42,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    results[alg.upper()] = res\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    print(f'{alg.upper():>5s}  R={res.r_factor:.4f}  iter={res.n_iterations:4d}  time={res.elapsed_seconds:.2f}s')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# R-factor comparison bar chart\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_r_factor_comparison(results)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_r_factor_comparison.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Multi-algorithm comparison grid\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_crystallography_comparison(pattern, results)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_algorithm_comparison.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('\\\\nSaved: cryst_r_factor_comparison.png, cryst_algorithm_comparison.png')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 5. Electron Density Maps\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"The recovered phases combined with the measured amplitudes allow us to compute\\n\",\n",
    "        \"the **electron density** via inverse Fourier transform:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"$$\\\\rho(\\\\mathbf{r}) = \\\\sum_{\\\\mathbf{h}} |F(\\\\mathbf{h})| \\\\exp[i\\\\varphi(\\\\mathbf{h})] \\\\exp(-2\\\\pi i\\\\, \\\\mathbf{h}\\\\cdot\\\\mathbf{r})$$\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"The electron density peaks reveal atom positions in the unit cell.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Best result\\n\",\n",
    "        \"best_alg = min(results, key=lambda k: results[k].r_factor)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"best = results[best_alg]\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'Best algorithm: {best_alg} (R = {best.r_factor:.4f})')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"fig = plot_electron_density(best)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"save_figure(fig, OUTPUT_DIR / 'cryst_electron_density.png')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"plt.close(fig)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('Saved: cryst_electron_density.png')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## 6. More Crystal Structures\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"Let's apply the same pipeline to additional crystal structures to demonstrate\\n\",\n",
    "        \"versatility.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "      \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Diamond structure (cubic, space group Fd-3m)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"diamond = CrystalStructure(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    cod_id='1010927',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    formula='C',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    space_group='F d -3 m',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    a=3.5670, b=3.5670, c=3.5670,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    atoms=[\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='C1', symbol='C', x=0.0, y=0.0, z=0.0),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='C2', symbol='C', x=0.25, y=0.25, z=0.25),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    ],\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"# Quartz (trigonal, SiO2)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"quartz = CrystalStructure(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    cod_id='1011097',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    formula='SiO2',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    space_group='P 32 2 1',\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    a=4.9134, b=4.9134, c=5.4052,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    alpha=90.0, beta=90.0, gamma=120.0,\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    atoms=[\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='Si1', symbol='Si', x=0.4697, y=0.0, z=0.0),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        AtomSite(label='O1', symbol='O', x=0.4135, y=0.2669, z=0.1191),\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    ],\\n\",\n",
    "        \")\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"structures = {'NaCl': nacl, 'Diamond': diamond, 'Quartz': quartz}\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print(f'{\\\"Crystal\\\":>10s}  {\\\"R-factor\\\":>10s}  {\\\"Iter\\\":>6s}  {\\\"Time (s)\\\":>10s}')\\n\",\n",
    "        \"print('-' * 45)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"for name, crystal in structures.items():\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    pat = simulate_diffraction(crystal, grid_size=GRID_SIZE)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    res = run_crystallography_retrieval(\\n\",\n",
    "        \"        pat, algorithm_name='raar', max_iterations=200, random_seed=42\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "        \"    print(f'{name:>10s}  {res.r_factor:10.4f}  {res.n_iterations:6d}  {res.elapsed_seconds:10.2f}')\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## Summary\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"This notebook demonstrated that the **same iterative phase-retrieval algorithms**\\n\",\n",
    "        \"used for astronomical wavefront sensing can be directly applied to\\n\",\n",
    "        \"**X-ray crystallographic data**:\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- The diffraction intensity $|F(h,k)|^2$ plays the role of the PSF intensity\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- The crystallographic R-factor replaces the Strehl ratio as quality metric\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Recovered phases → inverse FFT → electron density map\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- HIO and RAAR typically give the best results, matching known behaviour\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"For real-world data, use the COD download functions or the web UI to fetch\\n\",\n",
    "        \"CIF files from the Crystallography Open Database.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    }\n",
    "  ],\n",
